message.entry: Incorrect function handle. The Link weight function signature must be: function [cost] = functionName(STATE1,STATE2) or function [cost] = functionName(STATEID1,STATEID2,GRAPHOBJ).

The number of rows in 'Name' argument must be equal to the number of states.

stateData argument must be a column vector of character vectors, column vector of string scalars, cell array of character vectors, matrix with each row representing a state vector, or table that has all columns identical to the States table.
Link.EndStates have stateID which is not present. Expected EndStates to be an array with all of the values less than or equal to {0}.
Code generation is not supported for this function.
navGraph is empty. Links cannot be added without states.

入力の列名は ''{0}'' table の列と一致しなければなりません。
